A lot of people change their lens of someone when they find out they don’t have a home. Why is that? Are you inherently bad if you live on the streets?  The answer is no. A select few know this but  once upon a time I had no where to sleep except in my car my grey Hyundai accent was my home. I was in cosmetology school and at the time, all of my money went to school and for a reason I don’t wish to share for now, I found myself not having a place to go. I was one of the lucky ones to at least have my car as my home for a short period, before a friend took notice of me leaving class and never really leaving the lot and offered me to share her bed. HER BED! Her dad would buy me lunch sometimes which means more than I think they’ll ever really know because the loneliness of no home. Isolation and limited human connection. Fear. Fear of what people will think. Shame. Self induced shame of what people will think. Always about what people will think. I know this is a lot about me but I just wanted to prove a point that it doesn’t fucking matter. We’re just people trying to figure out life and just because shit is low doesn’t mean it can’t go high. 
  This is Danny, he introduced himself later as Dan the man, then muttered “well I used to be Dan the man” and that absolutely crushed me to hear. I see myself in Danny I understand deep shame so I did not ask why he had no home. He’s only 26, and has an amazing spirit about him and I think he will find his way. He really wants to be famous, I’m certainly not but I figured the least I could do was share this photo of us that I love thank you @savannajacoby for capturing it. he has a hilarious sense of humor. He showered me with compliments on my smile while discounting his own and as you can see in this photo he’s beaming with joy regardless of the societal smile standard. And BTW he asked for absolutely nothing from me.

The LV strap around the hat is actually very sentimental to me. It came from a bag that was gifted to me from a friend who committed suicide. I never felt comfortable using the bag for some reason, coming from humble beginnings, I often feel like an imposter carrying around a high end bag so it’s a surprise I said ok let’s cut it up but I’ve already honored my friend so much more with use, by adding it to my hat.
